  - The tracks are shorter (2–3 minutes) than my favored concise singles window (3–4.5 minutes) and the “radio‑ready” framing implies production choices made for mass appeal rather than preserving natural dynamics and guitar grit.
Overall, CD 2 aligns far more closely with the core of my stated preferences: guitar‑forward arrangements, natural room and analogue warmth, preserved dynamics and restrained remastering, tasteful keys and supportive harmonies, and tight rhythmic feel. CD 1 contains some positive elements but leans into radio polish, multitracked vocal sheen, minimal ambience and trimmed singles — all features I purposely avoid—so I reject it.

