Decision summary:
- I choose Journey because it best aligns with the majority of my explicit preferences: concise, hook‑forward songs; present intimate vocals with micro‑detail; economical synth/pad usage that supports rather than competes with the vocal; and—crucially—restored micro‑dynamics, generous headroom and low‑compression mastering that preserve transient snap. Those are core priorities for me and are spelled out in the Journey description.
- I reject the funk/R&B grooves not because it lacks many of the qualities I like (it has groove, roomed vocals and analogue warmth), but because it leaves open two risk areas that conflict with my dislikes: potential for extended, soaring solos and only “modest” compression rather than the low‑compression, headroom‑preserving mastering I explicitly value. Those differences make Journey the closer match to my stated sonic and structural preferences.

